VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT \b(?:danger_accept_invalid_certs|danger_accept_invalid_hostnames)\s*\(\s*true\s*\)
WHEN EXPR MISSING:test|development|localhost|staging
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects disabled TLS certificate or hostname validation.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Potential TLS Verification Bypass.
